      <dsc>
         <c id="ref11" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Topical Files, 1966-1999</unittitle>
               <unitid>Series I</unitid>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_2758b13070ebe742963c55d46d6fee01">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Arranged alphabetically, the series includes research materials used by Paul and Carole Bass. It also includes administrative files relating to the <title render="italic">
                     <part>New Haven Independent</part>
                  </title>, a weekly independent newspaper with an emphasis on investigative journalism, published in the late 1980s. Materials related to the American Independent Movement consist of FBI files obtained by Paul Bass through a Freedom Of Information Act request, and they document the activities of a leftist radical group functioning in New Haven during 1960s.</p>
            </scopecontent>
