         <c id="ref47" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Writings, 1977-2004</unittitle>
               <unitid>Series II</unitid>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_ca73fa1330f31dd53f5212dbceac13ac">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Arranged chronologically, the series consists of clippings of Paul Bass articles from the <title render="italic">
                     <part>Horace Mann Record</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>Reporter Dispatch</part>
                  </title> (White Plains, New York), <title render="italic">
                     <part>Yale Daily News</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>New Haven Register</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>Hartford Courant</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>New York Times</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>Fair Haven News</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>In These Times</part>
                  </title>, <title render="italic">
                     <part>New Haven Independent</part>
                  </title>, and <title render="italic">
                     <part>New Haven Advocate</part>
                  </title>. The series also contains clippings of Carole Bass articles from many of the same publications. The series ranges from when Paul Bass was a high school student at Horace Mann in New York to his time as an associate editor of the <title render="italic">
                     <part>New Haven Advocate</part>
                  </title>.</p>
               <p>The series reflects the careers of Paul and Carole Bass as investigative journalists primarily working in New Haven, Connecticut, and therefore documents most of the major news stories in the city from the early 1980s through the mid-2000s.</p>
            </scopecontent>
